He underlines the importance of monitoring the bats before carrying out maintenance on a property since the accidental destruction of a single breeding site could kill up to 400 females and young people, and perhaps wipe out an entire local population.
Flag mice are protected and it is illegal to kill them, harass them or disturb them or destroy their breeding grounds.
Elisabeth Ferrell, Scottish employee of the Bat Conservation Trust, has invited the audience to help with the work.
